# ✅ How to Optimize Performance **in JavaScript**

JavaScript performance optimization focuses on **reducing execution time**, **avoiding unnecessary work**, and **using memory efficiently**.

***

## 1️⃣ Avoid Unnecessary Computation

### ✅ Cache Expensive Results (Memoization)

```js
const memo = {};
function fibonacci(n) {
  if (memo[n]) return memo[n];
  if (n <= 1) return n;
  return memo[n] = fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2);
}
```

✅ Prevents repeated calculations  
✅ Reduces time complexity

***

## 2️⃣ Use Efficient Loops & Algorithms

### ❌ Slow (nested loops)

```js
for (let i of arr) {
  for (let j of arr) {
    // expensive
  }
}
```

### ✅ Faster (Map / Set)

```js
const set = new Set(arr);
set.has(value);
```

✅ Prefer:

*   `Map`, `Set` over objects
*   O(1) lookups

***

## 3️⃣ Minimize DOM Manipulation (Very Important 🔥)

### ❌ Bad

```js
for (let i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
  document.body.innerHTML += "<div></div>";
}
```

### ✅ Good (Batch updates)

```js
let html = "";
for (let i = 0; i < 1000; i++) {
  html += "<div></div>";
}
document.body.innerHTML = html;
```

✅ DOM operations are expensive  
✅ Update DOM **once**

***

## 4️⃣ Debouncing & Throttling

### ✅ Debounce (Search Input)

```js
function debounce(fn, delay) {
  let timer;
  return (...args) => {
    clearTimeout(timer);
    timer = setTimeout(() => fn(...args), delay);
  };
}
```

✅ Reduces excessive API calls  
✅ Improves UI responsiveness

***

## 5️⃣ Avoid Blocking the Call Stack

### ❌ Heavy synchronous task

```js
for (let i = 0; i < 1e9; i++) {}
```

### ✅ Break work using async

```js
setTimeout(() => {
  heavyTask();
});
```

✅ Keeps UI responsive  
✅ Avoids freezing the browser

***

## 6️⃣ Use Event Delegation

### ❌ Too many listeners

```js
buttons.forEach(btn =>
  btn.addEventListener("click", handler)
);
```

### ✅ Event delegation

```js
document.addEventListener("click", e => {
  if (e.target.matches(".btn")) {
    handler(e);
  }
});
```

✅ Fewer listeners  
✅ Less memory usage

***

## 7️⃣ Reduce Memory Leaks

### ✅ Clear Timers & Listeners

```js
const id = setInterval(task, 1000);
clearInterval(id);
```

✅ Remove unused references  
✅ Avoid global variables

***

## 8️⃣ Prefer `const` and `let` (Not `var`)

```js
const data = fetchData();
```

✅ Better scope control  
✅ Prevent accidental reassignment  
✅ Easier JS engine optimization

***

## 9️⃣ Use Asynchronous APIs

### ✅ Prefer async operations

```js
fetch("/api")
  .then(res => res.json())
  .then(data => console.log(data));
```

✅ Non‑blocking  
✅ Better performance than sync calls

***

## 🔟 Avoid Unnecessary Array Copies

### ❌ Expensive

```js
const newArr = arr.map(x => x);
```

### ✅ Better

```js
const newArr = [...arr]; // when needed
```

✅ Avoid copying unless required

***

## 1️⃣1️⃣ Use Web Workers for Heavy Tasks

```js
const worker = new Worker("worker.js");
worker.postMessage(data);
```

✅ Offloads heavy computation  
✅ Keeps main thread responsive

***

## 1️⃣2️⃣ Optimize Conditions & Logic

### ❌ Inefficient

```js
if (x === 1 || x === 2 || x === 3)
```

### ✅ Better

```js
if ([1, 2, 3].includes(x))
```

✅ Cleaner  
✅ Easier to optimize

***

